Use the standard library
This is how to move_one_ball of arr:
   Remember that n is arr's length
   When n is less than 2, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   Remember that drops is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that j is sum of i and 1
      When item i in arr is more than item j in arr, then:
         Increase drops
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   When item diff of n and 1 in arr is more than item 0 in arr, then:
      Increase drops
   End when
   When drops is at most 1, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   The answer is 0
Now you know
>>> move_one_ball of [3, 4, 5, 1, 2]
1
>>> move_one_ball of [3, 5, 4, 1, 2]
0
>>> move_one_ball of [3, 4, 5, 1, 2]
1